==English==
===Etymology===
From ''William Tutin'', an English [[manufacturer]]

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪniə|-eɪniə]]

===Noun===
'''tutania'''
#''(metallurgy)'' An alloy of [[copper]], [[antimony]], [[zinc]] and [[tin]] patented in 1770 by William Tutin, whose [[firm]] used it in commercial production of [[houseware|housewares]].